# Windsurf Rules for QA Utils

You are working on QA Utils — a monorepo with 45+ QA tools built with React 18, TypeScript, Bootstrap 5, and Vite.

## Commands to Run Before Committing
- `npm run lint` — 0 errors, max 221 warnings
- `npm test` — 928+ tests must pass
- `npm run build` — TypeScript + Vite build must succeed

## Project Structure
- `src/config/navigationConfig.ts` — Single source of truth for routes/nav/search
- `src/components/utils/` — Tool components (one per tool)
- `src/utils/` — Business logic modules
- `src/index.css` — CSS variables for light/dark theming
- `src/App.tsx` — Routes and lazy imports
- Tests: co-located in `__tests__/` directories

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` without justification
- Functional React components with hooks
- ARIA labels on all interactive elements
- CSS variables for colors: `var(--text)`, `var(--primary)`, `var(--bg)`, `var(--border-color)`
- Tool components use `tool-header`, `tool-card`, `tool-card-header`, `tool-card-body` CSS classes
- Mobile-first responsive design (min 375px width)
- Support light and dark themes — never hardcode colors

## Adding a New Tool
1. Create `src/utils/myTool.ts` and `src/components/utils/MyTool.tsx`
2. Add entry to `src/config/navigationConfig.ts`
3. Add lazy import + route in `src/App.tsx`
4. Add tests in `__tests__/`
5. Run lint + test + build

## Common Pitfalls
- Unused variables/imports cause TypeScript build errors
- Empty arrow functions `() => {}` cause lint errors — add a comment inside
- Changing component text/labels without updating tests breaks CI
- Hardcoded colors break dark theme
- Missing ARIA labels fail accessibility standards
